name: Catrin 1
description: At present it is common to associate the Day of the Dead, celebrated in Mexico, with the figure of one who is tall, wears a hat and is on the bones but still dresses elegantly. La Catrina has become an icon of Mexican popular culture, present both in Mexico and abroad to represent the Latin American country, especially on the day of the year destined to celebrate and make fun of death. However, the catrina represents more than just an image of those who are no longer alive.
